DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       sigsetmask  sets  the  current  signal mask (those signals
       that are blocked from delivery).  Signals are  blocked  if
       the corresponding bit in mask is a 1; the macro sigmask is
       provided to construct the mask for a given signum.

       The system quietly disallows SIGKILL, SIGSTOP, or  SIGCONT
       from being blocked.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       The previous set of masked signals is returned.

